Hi

First of all I want to thank authors for a great tool, this tool is
really vital for me!

HP ZR2720w is a great monitor, but it lacks OSD display. It has
brightness control, though you can click +/- buttons to adjust
brightness, the current brightness value is not indicated (brightness
just changes quietly).

I was really happy to find that ZR2720w does not use brightness control,
but uses standard DDC/CI interface. And I was either happier that there
is an open source tool which runs on linux for controlling monitors over
DDC/CI.

So I can read current brightness values, I can implement presets, and I
even able to dim my monitor for evening by cron :)

I'd like to share probe results. I'm happy to have a brightness
control. But I'm curious what other values, marked with [???], do
control? I hesitate to change values (not to break some factory
calibrated values etc.).

